A bridge collapse in Minneapolis resulted in at least six deaths, with cars and trucks plunging into the Mississippi River.
Despite initial fears of terrorism, officials confirmed no such link.
The tragedy occurred during rush hour, with a school bus narrowly avoiding disaster.
Rescue efforts continue as up to 30 people remain missing.
The collapsed bridge, built in 1967, had a history of structural issues.
President Bush pledged federal support for rebuilding.
State inspections of similar bridges were ordered to prevent future tragedies.
The community mourns the lives lost in this devastating event.
